import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 10))
    sns.boxplot(x="income", y="country", data=data, ax=ax, palette="Set3")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of income across different countries?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Income")
    plt.ylabel("Country")
    plt.axvline(x=data['income'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Income: {:.2f}'.format(data['income'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.barplot(x="region", y="income", data=data, ci=None, color="b", ax=ax)
    sns.barplot(x="region", y="health", data=data, ci=None, color="r", ax=ax)
    ax.set_ylabel("Average Income and Health")
    ax.set_xlabel("Region")
    ax.legend(["Income", "Health"])
    plt.title("What is the average income and health of countries in each region?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
